# Folder Structure Rules

## 1. Features Folder (`features/[feature-name]/`)

**When to create a new feature folder:**

- New major functionality area (e.g., billing, reports, analytics)
- Self-contained module with multiple components
- Has its own data model and business logic

**What goes inside:**

```
features/[feature-name]/
├── components/        # REQUIRED: All UI components
├── data/             # COMMON: Mock data, constants
├── schemas/          # IF USING FORMS: Zod schemas
├── utils/            # COMMON: Helper functions
├── constants/        # RARE: Only if needed (e.g., chart configs)
├── hooks/            # RARE: Only if needed (feature-specific hooks)
└── contexts/         # RARE: Only if needed (feature-specific contexts)
```

**Rules:**

- Feature components should NOT import from other features
- Feature components CAN import from `components/`, `lib/`, `types/`, `stores/`
- Keep features self-contained and portable

## 2. App Folder (`app/`)

**Route Structure:**

```
app/
├── layout.tsx                 # Root layout
├── page.tsx                   # Root page
├── (auth)/                    # Auth routes (no dashboard layout)
│   └── login/
│       └── page.tsx
└── (dashboard)/               # Protected routes (with layout)
    ├── layout.tsx             # Dashboard layout wrapper
    ├── page.tsx               # Dashboard home
    └── [feature]/             # Feature routes
        ├── page.tsx
        └── [sub-route]/
            └── page.tsx
```

**File Requirements:**

- `page.tsx` - Route component (REQUIRED)
- `layout.tsx` - Shared layout (OPTIONAL)
- `loading.tsx` - Loading state (OPTIONAL)
- `error.tsx` - Error boundary (OPTIONAL)
- `not-found.tsx` - 404 page (OPTIONAL)

**Rules:**

- Routes should import from `features/`, not directly from feature subfolders
- Keep route files thin - delegate to feature components

## 3. Components Folder (`components/`)

**For shared components only:**

```
components/
├── ui/                    # shadcn/ui components (DON'T MODIFY STRUCTURE)
│   ├── button.tsx
│   ├── card.tsx
│   └── ...
└── layout/                # Layout components (header, sidebar, footer)
    ├── app-sidebar.tsx
    ├── site-header.tsx
    └── dashboard-footer.tsx
```

**Rules:**

- Only add components used across 3+ features
- Feature-specific components go in `features/[feature]/components/`
- UI primitives from shadcn/ui stay in `components/ui/`
- Don't modify shadcn/ui component structure

## 4. Types Folder (`types/`)

**PRIMARY LOCATION FOR ALL TYPES:**

```
types/
├── auth.types.ts              # Authentication & user types
├── api.types.ts               # API response types
├── billing.types.ts           # Billing feature types
├── toast.types.ts             # Toast notification types
└── index.ts                   # Type exports
```

**IMPORTANT RULES:**

- **ALL types go in `types/[feature].types.ts`** (centralized)
- Use `shared.types.ts` for types used across multiple features
- Never define types in component files
- Never define types in feature folders
- Export all types for reuse

## 5. Convex Folder (`convex/`)

**For Convex backend operations:**

```
convex/
├── _serverActions/        # Server-side actions
├── _schemas/              # Database schemas
├── _utilities/            # Convex utilities
├── [entity].ts            # Entity definitions (queries, mutations)
└── http.ts                # HTTP endpoints
```

**What goes here:**

- Database queries and mutations
- Server-side actions
- Database schemas
- HTTP endpoints

**Rules:**

- Keep entity files focused on one entity
- Use `_serverActions/` for complex server-side logic
- Update schemas in `_schemas/` when database structure changes

## 6. Utils Folder (`lib/`)

**For global utilities:**

```
lib/
├── utils.ts               # General utilities (cn helper, etc.)
├── date-utils.ts          # Date utilities
├── api-client.ts          # API client (if needed)
└── ...
```

**Feature-specific utilities go in:**

`features/[feature]/utils/[feature].utils.ts`

**Rules:**

- Only add utilities used across multiple features
- Feature-specific utilities stay in feature folders
- Keep functions pure and testable

## 7. Store Folder (`stores/`)

**For Zustand stores:**

```
stores/
├── navigation.store.ts    # UI state for navigation
├── app.store.ts          # Global app store
└── [feature].store.ts     # Feature-specific store
```

**Naming Convention:**

- `[feature-name].store.ts`
- Example: `user.store.ts`, `cart.store.ts`

**Important Guidelines:**

- Use a Zustand store when a feature requires shared state and actions that multiple components depend on
- Use `useState` when the state is local to a single component and does not need to be accessed or managed outside that component

## 8. Hooks Folder (`hooks/`)

**For global custom hooks:**

```
hooks/
├── use-convex-user.ts     # Convex user hook
├── use-mobile.tsx         # Mobile detection
└── use-toast.ts           # Toast notifications
```

**Rules:**

- Only add hooks used across multiple features
- Feature-specific hooks go in `features/[feature]/hooks/`

## 9. Styles Folder (`styles/`)

**For global styles:**

```
styles/
├── globals.css            # Global CSS
└── fonts.css              # Font definitions
```

**Rules:**

- Keep global styles minimal
- Use Tailwind CSS for most styling
- Feature-specific styles should use Tailwind classes

## 10. Public Folder (`public/`)

**For static assets:**

```
public/
├── images/                # Images
├── icons/                 # Icons
└── avatars/               # Avatar images
```

**Rules:**

- Organize assets by type
- Use descriptive folder names
- Keep file sizes optimized
